    <body>
        <p>A Flare community always corresponds to a Flare target. If you publish more that one online Flare target, you have these options:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Enable One Flare Community for All Targets </span>This creates one Pulse system and Flare community to use with all of your Flare targets. It also lets you run reports for the entire community.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Enable a Unique Flare Community for Each&#160;Target </span>This creates a separate Flare community and Pulse system for each Flare target. The benefit to this approach is that it lets you run reports for each community.</p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../../../Images/Shared/Fl-Pu/pulse_admin_system_find_systems.png" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </body>
